# Clerk UserButton Customization

Extend `<UserButton />` with custom actions, links, and pages using Clerk's built-in sub-components. Never build a separate settings menu outside of `<UserButton />`.

## Custom Menu Items

Two types of custom items are available:

- `<UserButton.Action>` — triggers an action or opens a custom profile page
- `<UserButton.Link>` — navigates to an internal or external URL

All custom items go inside `<UserButton.MenuItems>`.

## Adding an Action

```tsx
<UserButton>
  <UserButton.MenuItems>
    <UserButton.Action
      label="App Settings"
      labelIcon={<SettingsIcon />}
      open="app-settings"
    />
  </UserButton.MenuItems>

  <UserButton.UserProfilePage label="App Settings" labelIcon={<SettingsIcon />} url="app-settings">
    <div>
      <h1>App Settings</h1>
      <p>Custom settings content here</p>
    </div>
  </UserButton.UserProfilePage>
</UserButton>
```

## Adding a Link

```tsx
<UserButton>
  <UserButton.MenuItems>
    <UserButton.Link label="Pricing" labelIcon={<CreditCardIcon />} href="/pricing" />
  </UserButton.MenuItems>
</UserButton>
```

## Reordering Default Items

Target built-in items with `label="manageAccount"` or `label="signOut"` to reorder them:

```tsx
<UserButton.MenuItems>
  <UserButton.Action label="manageAccount" />
  <UserButton.Link label="Pricing" labelIcon={<CreditCardIcon />} href="/pricing" />
  <UserButton.Action label="signOut" />
</UserButton.MenuItems>
```

## Conditional Rendering

Gate menu items behind Clerk permissions or billing features:

```tsx
const { has, isLoaded } = useAuth();
if (!isLoaded) return null;

const isPro = has({ plan: "pro" });

<UserButton>
  {isPro && (
    <UserButton.MenuItems>
      <UserButton.Action label="Pro Settings" labelIcon={<StarIcon />} open="pro-settings" />
    </UserButton.MenuItems>
  )}
</UserButton>
```

## Rules

- All custom menu items must be placed inside `<UserButton.MenuItems>`
- Use `<UserButton.Action>` with `open` prop to link to a `<UserButton.UserProfilePage>`
- Use `<UserButton.Link>` for navigation — all three props (`label`, `labelIcon`, `href`) are required
- Use `label="manageAccount"` or `label="signOut"` to reorder default items — never recreate them
- Gate items behind Clerk `has()` checks when tied to billing plans or permissions
